					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Oh, I understand why you'd want a program to output .db statements. It's a lot easier to edit values with them. And plus, you can arrange them like:
<br />
<br />.db $32,$66
<br />.db $44
<br />.db $2F, $3F, $90
<br />
<br />So it's not like it is in a hex editor where it's just a sea of hex digits. I made a program a while back that output .db statements which held results of math functions for my sound engine. This may have been because I don't quite have the knowledge to make programs that save data to files (I'm pretty much a noob when it comes to file interaction).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/" class="postlink">-Owner of Poultry Games</a></div>
